The claim with the title 'Julius Malema’s SONA 2015 debate speech fact-checked ' says “ [o]nly 204,522 new entrant opportunities at universities were available this year. This is despite the fact that of the 532,860 grade 12 pupils who wrote matric in 2014, only 403,874 pupils passed with marks that allow them to study in tertiary universities either for a degree, diploma or a higher certificate. ”
